The user can choose which 3D he wants to see. The user can zoom-in, zoom-out and rotate the modelisation whith his fingers. You need to have something to have a maximum and minimum possible zoom. Each 3D have some descriptions (texts or images) in a scrollable area. Also, each one have some options. For example, the heart can be seen with a  cross-sectional view, we can see its echography, etc. We have also a slider to play with the severity of the heart disease.
